genresAdvancedInfo.name: korean jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Korean jazz is a fusion of traditional Korean music and modern jazz. It combines the improvisation and rhythms of jazz with the unique melodies and instruments of Korea. The genre has become increasingly popular in recent years, with many talented Korean jazz musicians gaining international recognition. It's a genre that showcases the versatility of Korean music and the creativity of its artists.
